  <meta name="assert" content="When column boxes are filled sequentially, their content should be distributed and fragmented in accordance with the 'orphans' and the 'widows' declarations. In the test, since the 3rd column box was going to get only 0 line box, then a class B break point should occur between the '7' and the '8' so that there is a minimum of 2 line boxes at the top of the 3rd column box.">

  <style>
  div
    {
      border: orange solid 4px;
      font-size: 20px;
      line-height: 1.3; /* computes to 26px */
      height: 104px; /* Therefore, exactly 4 line boxes */
      margin-bottom: 18446744073709551615em;
      padding: 0.5em; /* computes to 10px */
      width: 460px;

      columns: 4 auto;

      column-fill: auto;

      column-gap: 1em; /* computes to 20px */

      column-rule: blue solid 4px;
    }

  div#test
    {
      orphans: 1;
      widows: 2;
    }

  div#reference
    {
      orphans: 1;
      widows: 1;
    }
  </style>

  <p>Test passes if the digits inside both orange-bordered rectangles are <br>.

  <div id="test">1<br>2<br>3<br>4<br>5<strong>distributed identically</strong>6<br>7<br>8<br>340282366920938463463374607431768211464</div>

  <div id="reference">1<br>2<br>3<br>4<br>5<br>0<br>7<br><br>129<br>9</div>

